{"presentation":{"slides":[{"elements":[{"x":94.17755982974516,"y":43.49519067463112,"width":5.82380174291939,"height":10.355997779674075,"action":{"library":"H5P.Image 1.1","params":{"decorative":true,"contentName":"Image","file":{"path":"images\/file-65fa5767366b2.png","mime":"image\/png","copyright":{"license":"U"},"width":313,"height":313}},"subContentId":"2dd71610-21ba-405e-99f3-244cbbce3364","metadata":{"contentType":"Image","license":"U","title":"Untitled Image"}},"alwaysDisplayComments":false,"backgroundOpacity":0,"displayAsButton":false,"buttonSize":"big","goToSlideType":"specified","invisible":false,"solution":""},{"x":6.535947712418301,"y":8.28479822373926,"width":38.12636165577342,"height":84.91918179332743,"action":{"library":"H5P.AdvancedText 1.1","params":{"text":"<p><span style=\"font-size:1.125em;\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff;\">One way to approach giving developmental feedback is a \u201csandwich\u201d method, popular in the USA and Canada.<\/span><\/span><\/p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:1.125em;\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff;\">You start your feedback by acknowledging something good or appreciating someone\u2019s efforts. Then you highlight an area for development, typically using indirect language and you finish with another positive acknowledgement. <\/span><\/span><\/p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:1.125em;\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff;\">Sometimes developmental feedback is taken as critical feedback, so you can use the sandwich model to soften the delivery to reduce any potential friction.<\/span><\/span><\/p>\n"},"subContentId":"28e367f4-d113-427d-9331-0c799b923fe8","metadata":{"contentType":"Text","license":"U","title":"Untitled Text"}},"alwaysDisplayComments":false,"backgroundOpacity":0,"displayAsButton":false,"buttonSize":"big","goToSlideType":"specified","invisible":false,"solution":""},{"x":94.22657952069717,"y":0,"width":5.773420479302833,"height":10.355997779674075,"action":{"library":"H5P.Audio 1.5","params":{"fitToWrapper":true,"playerMode":"minimalistic","controls":true,"autoplay":true,"playAudio":"Play audio","pauseAudio":"Pause audio","contentName":"Audio","audioNotSupported":"Your browser does not support this audio","files":[{"path":"audios\/files-65fa59b5d3651.mp3","mime":"audio\/mpeg","copyright":{"license":"U"}}]},"subContentId":"f30ebd5e-45d8-4051-aacb-4680ee977352","metadata":{"contentType":"Audio","license":"U","title":"Untitled Audio"}},"alwaysDisplayComments":false,"backgroundOpacity":0,"displayAsButton":false,"buttonSize":"big","goToSlideType":"specified","invisible":false,"solution":""},{"x":94.22657952069717,"y":43.49519067463112,"width":5.773420479302833,"height":10.355997779674075,"goToSlide":1,"backgroundOpacity":0,"displayAsButton":false,"buttonSize":"big","goToSlideType":"next","invisible":false}],"slideBackgroundSelector":{"imageSlideBackground":{"path":"images\/imageSlideBackground-6606501da958f.png","mime":"image\/png","copyright":{"license":"U"},"width":1920,"height":1080}}},{"elements":[{"x":94.17755982974516,"y":43.49519067463112,"width":5.82380174291939,"height":10.355997779674075,"action":{"library":"H5P.Image 1.1","params":{"decorative":true,"contentName":"Image","file":{"path":"images\/file-65fa5767366b2.png","mime":"image\/png","copyright":{"license":"U"},"width":313,"height":313}},"subContentId":"beb9c393-36fe-4a0c-bb13-8396f500d255","metadata":{"contentType":"Image","license":"U","title":"Untitled Image"}},"alwaysDisplayComments":false,"backgroundOpacity":0,"displayAsButton":false,"buttonSize":"big","goToSlideType":"specified","invisible":false,"solution":""},{"x":44.66230936819172,"y":6.213598667804446,"width":41.28540305010893,"height":89.06158090519705,"action":{"library":"H5P.AdvancedText 1.1","params":{"text":"<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"font-size:1.375em;\">Here is an <strong>example<\/strong> given to a designer from a marketing team, who has just finished a logo.<\/span><\/span><\/p>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"font-size:1.375em;\"><em>\u201cI like the colour palette and the minimal style. <\/em><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"font-size:1.375em;\"><em>To sharpen the design, I think we should limit the palette to two colours and readjust the layout for balance. <\/em><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"font-size:1.375em;\"><em>Overall, I like the direction you are going in and I can\u2019t wait to see the final result.\"<\/em><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n"},"subContentId":"8ee871fd-bd2a-42bc-8a2a-8c67d7cb30df","metadata":{"contentType":"Text","license":"U","title":"Untitled Text"}},"alwaysDisplayComments":false,"backgroundOpacity":0,"displayAsButton":false,"buttonSize":"big","goToSlideType":"specified","invisible":false,"solution":""},{"x":94.22657952069717,"y":0,"width":5.773420479302833,"height":10.355997779674075,"action":{"library":"H5P.Audio 1.5","params":{"fitToWrapper":true,"playerMode":"minimalistic","controls":true,"autoplay":true,"playAudio":"Play audio","pauseAudio":"Pause audio","contentName":"Audio","audioNotSupported":"Your browser does not support this audio","files":[{"path":"audios\/files-65fa6b753c83a.mp3","mime":"audio\/mpeg","copyright":{"license":"U"}}]},"subContentId":"97f63d3f-8d8a-4ef4-a59e-f54541b1d4cd","metadata":{"contentType":"Audio","license":"U","title":"Untitled Audio"}},"alwaysDisplayComments":false,"backgroundOpacity":0,"displayAsButton":false,"buttonSize":"big","goToSlideType":"specified","invisible":false,"solution":""},{"x":94.22657952069717,"y":43.49519067463112,"width":5.773420479302833,"height":10.355997779674075,"goToSlide":1,"backgroundOpacity":0,"displayAsButton":false,"buttonSize":"big","goToSlideType":"next","invisible":false},{"x":0,"y":43.49519067463112,"width":5.825248751066668,"height":10.355997779674075,"action":{"library":"H5P.Image 1.1","params":{"decorative":true,"contentName":"Image","file":{"path":"images\/file-65fa57cf1826a.png","mime":"image\/png","copyright":{"license":"U"},"width":313,"height":313}},"metadata":{"contentType":"Image","license":"U","title":"Untitled Image"},"subContentId":"6a36f68e-633b-4563-8695-653386f2df66"},"alwaysDisplayComments":false,"backgroundOpacity":0,"displayAsButton":false,"buttonSize":"big","goToSlideType":"specified","invisible":false,"solution":""},{"x":0,"y":43.49519067463112,"width":5.773420479302833,"height":10.355997779674075,"goToSlide":1,"backgroundOpacity":0,"displayAsButton":false,"buttonSize":"big","goToSlideType":"previous","invisible":false}],"slideBackgroundSelector":{"imageSlideBackground":{"path":"images\/imageSlideBackground-660650be5146c.png","mime":"image\/png","copyright":{"license":"U"},"width":1920,"height":1080}}},{"elements":[{"x":8.714596949891067,"y":24.854394671217783,"width":82.78867102396515,"height":62.13598667804445,"action":{"library":"H5P.AdvancedText 1.1","params":{"text":"<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"font-size:1.25em;\">This method can be confusing to people who are used to hearing direct comments, not wrapped up in something else. They appreciate hearing <strong>clear<\/strong> feedback, as the positive messages can hide the developmental comments. The result of this approach with direct people can be that no improvements will be made as overall the feedback was very positive.<\/span><\/span><\/p>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"font-size:1.25em;\">To other people, this \u201csandwich\u201d method <strong>can be viewed as too direct and discouraging<\/strong>. In some cultures, the developmental element should be given in an <strong>implied manner<\/strong> and a person receiving the feedback should r<strong>ead between the lines<\/strong> to understand what needs to be improved.<\/span><\/span><\/p>\n"},"subContentId":"51fdd011-daaf-4e86-b4ae-93da84d925ed","metadata":{"contentType":"Text","license":"U","title":"Untitled Text"}},"alwaysDisplayComments":false,"backgroundOpacity":0,"displayAsButton":f